news.title: Ludhiana development body set to take action against builders of illegal colonies
news.para: Glada had recommended that tehsildars not register plots in unauthorised colonies, PSPCL refrain from issuing electricity connections and FIRs be filed against developers of such colonies in Ludhiana district.

news.title: Mindspace REIT raises Rs 340 crore through NCDs
news.para: The issuance is rated CRISIL AAA/Stable and [ICRA] AAA(Stable) by CRISIL Ratings and ICRA respectively. The tenure of debentures is three years at a fixed coupon of 7.93% per annum payable quarterly.

news.title: Prestige Group acquires 62.5 acres land in Indirapuram Extension
news.para: Prestige Group's project spans over 10 million sq ft of saleable area, with a projected gross development value (GDV) surpassing Rs 10,000 crore.

news.title: Mumbai's elite lap up vacation homes for privacy & exclusivity
news.para: Government initiatives aimed at improving connectivity are also catalysing real estate development in the area, elevating its appeal among developers, homebuyers, and investors.

news.title: Dubai’s ‘sustainable city’ was supposed to start a trend. It hasn’t yet
news.para: After a push for greener development in the early aughts, and despite big promises at the United Nations’ climate conference in Dubai last year, the United Arab Emirates is still severely lacking in buildings and communities that speak to its environmental goals.

news.title: Tata Projects leases 1.2 lakh sq ft office space in Mumbai's Powai
news.para: The company has leased the space in commercial tower Cignus Powai, which is a project of K Raheja Corp's hospitality business Chalet Hotels, for a total term of five years. The Tata Son’s subsidiary will be paying rentals of nearly Rs 86 crores through the entire tenure of the lease.

news.title: Karnataka government proposes allowing more FAR for a premium
news.para: In a notification published on March 16, the govt released a draft amendment to the Karnataka Planning Authorities Rules, 1965, and invited objections/suggestions, if any, within seven days.

news.title: Twenty-Five Downtown Realty raised Rs 250 crore from Oaktree
news.para: It raised the money amid an ongoing dispute with DLF and Shapoorji group, which alleged that a Hubtown-linked entity connived with Omkara ARC and PNB Housing Finance to gain control over a company that has land assets valuing Rs 10,000 crore.

news.title: Allottees fume as Delhi development body flats still not ready in Dwarka
news.para: The allottees have claimed that finishing and infrastructure work were still in progress and DDA had not yet obtained all statutory permissions.

news.title: China: Shares of Radiance Holdings plunge after missed bond repayment
news.para: Beijing-based Radiant becomes the latest property firm to miss an offshore debt payment since a debt crisis engulfed the industry in mid-2021, leading to many defaults, such as those of China Evergrande Group and Country Garden.

news.title: Enforcement directorate conducts searches at G Square across 20 locations
news.para: As per the sources, raids were also conducted in houses and properties allegedly linked to G Square in more than 20 places, including Mylapore, Alwarpet, East Coast Road, Adyar, Neelangarai, and Anna Nagar.

news.title: Now, green credits for compensatory afforestation
news.para: The Centre has finally notified the methodology for Green Credit Rules, 2023. As per the methodology, green credit shall be calculated at the rate of one green credit per tree growth through tree plantation.

news.title: Bidhannagar civic body plans special teams for six boroughs to inspect illegal buildings
news.para: Sources from BMC said the civic body planned to form special teams for each of the six boroughs to inspect if the upcoming buildings were being constructed according to civic rules.

news.title: Hyderabad development body's official suspended for faulty TDRs
news.para: Hyderabad Metropolitan Development Authority also called for an explanation from the planning officer of the zone concerned.

news.title: Jaipur: JMC-Heritage attaches 35 properties over urban development tax
news.para: JMC-Heritage commissioner Abhishek Surana said, "Despite repeated notices, no information was given to the zone offices by the property holders. Due to which the revenue branch took action against the property holders and attached 35 properties.”

news.title: Now, commercial buildings in Chandigarh to follow energy efficiency code
news.para: The code will come into effect from May 1, 2024. Its aim is to make commercial building energy efficient, and help save 20-30% electricity every year.

news.title: Gurugram: Soon, own enforcement & land procurement cells for GMDA to check encroachments
news.para: The enforcement cell will carry out surveys in 42 villages, falling within the authority's jurisdiction, to identify illegal construction. They will also work on procurement of land for developing infrastructure projects in the city.

news.title: Omkara ARC acquires Park Hyatt Hyderabad's bad loans at 34% discount
news.para: The all-cash deal involved Omkara paying ₹300 crore to buy the ₹450 crore principal outstanding of Park Hyatt in Hyderabad, a 5-star luxury hotel consisting of more than 200 rooms including 25 suites and 40 serviced apartments in Hyderabad. The total debt outstanding including interest and principal is ₹700 crore.

news.title: SWAMIH fund approves Rs 340 crore for Vatika project in Gurugram
news.para: The project, spanning 14 acres, boasts a saleable area of 1.4 million square feet. Initiated nearly a decade ago, it comprises approximately 640 apartments, with 150 units sold prior to SWAMIH's involvement.

news.title: Provide parking space to flat bought from landowner, court tells Bengaluru builder
news.para: In addition, the firm was asked to pay Rs 20,000 to the complainant for the mental agony caused to him, and another Rs 10,000 as litigation cost within two months.
